The paper deals with distributed algorithms for computing the minimum cut in a network, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve sampling, approximation, and dynamic programming, which are common in the areas of networking (cs.NI), algorithms (cs.AL), and game theory (cs.GT).
